1
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,200
Pick up the phone.

2
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:16,120
Hello, Brother Wang.

3
00:01:16,599 --> 00:01:17,959
Can you ship those vegetables in?

4
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,400
Your road is closed too?

5
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:23,920
All right.

6
00:01:24,319 --> 00:01:25,359
I'll figure it out myself.

7
00:01:25,959 --> 00:01:26,799
Thanks, Brother Wang.

8
00:01:28,799 --> 00:01:30,519
Party Secretary, Brother Haozi.

9
00:01:30,959 --> 00:01:32,439
No vegetables can get in from nearby.

10
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:34,000
So what are we going to eat tomorrow?

11
00:01:34,519 --> 00:01:36,239
Our guests from Shanghai, Hainan,

12
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,319
and Guangdong,

13
00:01:37,519 --> 00:01:38,840
can't just eat potatoes every day.

14
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:40,519
Besides,

15
00:01:40,879 --> 00:01:43,159
we don't even have enough potatoes left.

16
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:44,159
Don't worry.

17
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,480
We'll think of something.

18
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,079
Three guesthouses,

19
00:01:47,079 --> 00:01:48,079
over a hundred guests.

20
00:01:48,959 --> 00:01:49,400
I mean,

21
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,599
where do we get vegetables at this hour?

22
00:01:50,599 --> 00:01:50,959
We...

23
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:51,640
Haoran.

24
00:01:52,359 --> 00:01:52,599
Um...

25
00:01:52,599 --> 00:01:53,560
that guy from Zengba Village last year,

26
00:01:53,719 --> 00:01:54,719
contact him right away.

27
00:01:55,439 --> 00:01:56,239
Okay, okay, okay.

28
00:01:56,239 --> 00:01:56,560
Got it.

29
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,120
Party Secretary.

30
00:01:57,519 --> 00:01:58,040
Party Secretary.

31
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,400
Dr. Meiduo, Zhaxi.

32
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,000
You're here.

33
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,439
The road authority said

34
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:04,120
it opens the day after tomorrow at best.

35
00:02:04,719 --> 00:02:05,319
Day after tomorrow?

36
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:06,439
Day after tomorrow?

37
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,439
Then what do we do tomorrow?

38
00:02:08,639 --> 00:02:09,680
All I've got left is potatoes.

39
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:12,240
Brother Jimei said to add pickled radish.

40
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:14,560
But they came for our highland cuisine.

41
00:02:14,879 --> 00:02:16,159
Just potatoes and pickled radish all day?

42
00:02:16,159 --> 00:02:16,840
That's just not right.

43
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:18,719
So what do we do?

44
00:02:19,159 --> 00:02:20,919
Some people are already posting online

45
00:02:20,919 --> 00:02:22,319
saying we're a food desert.

46
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,080
If they eat potatoes for two more days,

47
00:02:24,319 --> 00:02:25,639
who'd ever dare come here again?

48
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:26,520
Okay, here's what we do.

49
00:02:26,599 --> 00:02:27,639
Let's keep calling around now,

50
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:28,400
keep calling.

51
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,360
Come on, come on.

52
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,680
Hurry, hurry, get on the phone.

53
00:02:31,759 --> 00:02:32,560
Zhaxi.

54
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,800
Quick, Zhaxi, open the door.

55
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:36,319
Here.

56
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:37,599
Give me a hand.

57
00:02:40,719 --> 00:02:41,240
Close the door.

58
00:02:42,039 --> 00:02:42,840
This snow's coming down

59
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:43,840
so heavy.

60
00:02:44,319 --> 00:02:45,039
Uncle Liu.

61
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,120
What brings you here?

62
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,479
I heard the guests at our guesthouse

63
00:02:48,479 --> 00:02:49,800
have no vegetables to eat.

64
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,319
We're still making calls.

65
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,439
We're working on it.

66
00:02:53,599 --> 00:02:54,439
I brought some for you.

67
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:57,680
This much?

68
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:01,680
Uncle Liu,

69
00:03:02,479 --> 00:03:03,639
these vegetables aren't ripe yet, right?

70
00:03:05,199 --> 00:03:06,280
They're two days short,

71
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,560
but they're edible.

72
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:09,680
You pulled them before they were ready.

73
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:11,560
So I pulled them, no big deal.

74
00:03:12,319 --> 00:03:13,599
I'd have to pull them soon anyway.

75
00:03:13,919 --> 00:03:15,759
But if you let these grow a few more days,

76
00:03:15,759 --> 00:03:17,000
you could've sold them for a good price.

77
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:17,800
Right now,

78
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,159
the price doesn't matter anymore.

79
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,960
What matters most now

80
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:25,280
is making sure the guests get vegetables.

81
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:27,080
Our village is developing tourism,

82
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,680
so many guests have come,

83
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:31,080
and if they can't even get vegetables,

84
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:33,400
who'd ever come back after that?

85
00:03:33,719 --> 00:03:34,199
Right?

86
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,599
My test field had a problem,

87
00:03:36,599 --> 00:03:37,479
and you're helping me out like this.

88
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:38,400
But...

89
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,520
will your greenhouse hold up?

90
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,080
My greenhouse doesn't matter.

91
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,759
Make sure you take good care of yours.

92
00:03:48,439 --> 00:03:50,039
Those veggies in there are precious.

93
00:03:52,199 --> 00:03:52,719
Don't just stand there.

94
00:03:52,919 --> 00:03:53,719
Quick, quick, unload the truck.

95
00:03:53,719 --> 00:03:54,439
Come on, come on.

96
00:03:58,319 --> 00:03:59,039
Party Secretary.

97
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:00,080
Are these vegetables enough?

98
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,000
I'll get more if not.

99
00:04:01,439 --> 00:04:02,039
That's plenty.

100
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:03,360
Old Liu.

101
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,199
What you did today,

102
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,120
the whole village will remember.

103
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,759
It doesn't matter if they remember.

104
00:04:10,879 --> 00:04:12,000
As long as everyone enjoys the food,

105
00:04:12,159 --> 00:04:12,919
my heart

106
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,039
is full of joy.

107
00:04:15,159 --> 00:04:15,919
I've got to hurry off now.

108
00:04:16,639 --> 00:04:18,639
A lot of folks are low on vegetables too.

109
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,639
Especially the primary school cafeteria.

110
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:21,800
If I don't get them there today,

111
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,000
the kids will go hungry tomorrow.

112
00:04:23,519 --> 00:04:23,879
Alright.

113
00:04:23,879 --> 00:04:24,319
I'm off.

114
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:25,279
Stay safe out there.

115
00:04:25,279 --> 00:04:26,160
I'll go with you.

116
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:26,920
What for?

117
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:27,800
You should hurry.

118
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:28,759
Hurry, hurry.

119
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:29,639
I can manage on my own.

120
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:30,560
The snow's so heavy.

121
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:31,600
What about your rheumatism?

122
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:32,399
I'll drive you.

123
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:34,759
Get these vegetables to the inn quickly.

124
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,120
Make sure the guests can eat.

125
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:36,959
That's what matters most.

126
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:37,959
After I drop you off, I'll—

127
00:04:37,959 --> 00:04:38,439
Zhaxi.

128
00:04:39,399 --> 00:04:40,800
The older you get, the less you listen.

129
00:04:43,279 --> 00:04:43,720
Dear,

130
00:04:44,519 --> 00:04:45,759
take good care of that greenhouse.

131
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,920
Those little seedlings in there

132
00:04:49,199 --> 00:04:50,399
are the hope of our village.

133
00:04:51,319 --> 00:04:51,959
You got that?

134
00:04:53,879 --> 00:04:54,319
I'm off.

135
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:56,360
Open the door.

136
00:04:58,800 --> 00:04:59,319
Take it easy, Uncle.

137
00:04:59,519 --> 00:04:59,959
I'm heading out.

138
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:00,639
Drive carefully.

139
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,160
Be careful.

140
00:06:11,959 --> 00:06:14,079
Someone asked, "What is home?"

141
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,439
Home is when the storm comes,

142
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,600
someone fixes the roof for you.

143
00:06:19,279 --> 00:06:20,360
When disaster strikes,

144
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:23,639
someone gives you their last bit of food.

145
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:34,720
Party Secretary,

146
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:39,160
this is the old land lease agreement.

147
00:06:41,839 --> 00:06:42,439
This land,

148
00:06:44,319 --> 00:06:44,879
I'll give it back.

149
00:06:49,279 --> 00:06:49,800
Old Liu,

150
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,600
we're still fighting for the compensation.

151
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,600
Party Secretary,

152
00:06:55,199 --> 00:06:55,959
don't forget,

153
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,759
I'm also a villager of Taohua Village.

154
00:06:59,319 --> 00:07:01,920
Now Taohua Village must grow and prosper.

155
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,879
I can't get in the way of such big plans.

156
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,560
As for the compensation,

157
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:07,720
whatever the village decides is fine.

158
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:08,759
If there isn't any,

159
00:07:09,519 --> 00:07:10,560
I won't take a single cent.

160
00:07:11,959 --> 00:07:13,000
Don't read too much into it.

161
00:07:13,519 --> 00:07:14,480
I'm not that noble.

162
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,800
More than twenty years ago,

163
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,439
when I first came to our village,

164
00:07:21,199 --> 00:07:22,199
it was Uncle Duoji

165
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:24,360
who carried bamboo over for me.

166
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,959
Auntie Zhuoma sewed the curtains.

167
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:30,439
The whole village came out to help.

168
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,519
Those with materials gave materials,

169
00:07:33,199 --> 00:07:33,959
and those without

170
00:07:34,199 --> 00:07:35,279
helped me with their labor.

171
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:37,839
That's how these greenhouses got built.

172
00:07:40,279 --> 00:07:41,360
What I'll never forget the most

173
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,480
is your grandfather.

174
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:46,959
Your grandfather,

175
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:49,000
worried that being from the mainland,

176
00:07:49,759 --> 00:07:51,279
I couldn't handle the cold here.

177
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,639
So he took the only

178
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,839
yak hide mattress your family had

179
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:59,160
and laid it on my bed.

180
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,639
That kindness,

181
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:05,600
I, Old Liu,

182
00:08:06,639 --> 00:08:07,839
will never forget it.

183
00:08:10,279 --> 00:08:12,120
A village school teacher told a story

184
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,720
called The Farmer and the Snake.

185
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,920
I understood that story.

186
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,560
For most of my life,

187
00:08:18,839 --> 00:08:20,160
I've drunk this village's water,

188
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,439
and farmed this village's land.

189
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:23,519
Now our village wants to develop,

190
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:24,639
to prosper.

191
00:08:25,639 --> 00:08:26,399
At a time like this,

192
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:28,279
if I stand in the way,

193
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:31,040
wouldn't I be that snake?

194
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:33,960
All right, enough talk.

195
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:35,559
Tear it down.

196
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,279
Tear it down.

197
00:08:36,759 --> 00:08:37,240
You all get back to work.

198
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:38,519
Uncle,

199
00:08:38,639 --> 00:08:39,360
don't go, please don't go.

200
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:41,080
Have a seat, please sit down.

201
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:41,960
Sit, sit, sit, sit, sit.

202
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:45,480
You have to give us a chance

203
00:08:46,759 --> 00:08:47,799
to repay you this time.

204
00:08:51,519 --> 00:08:52,080
Old Liu,

205
00:08:52,679 --> 00:08:53,639
Haoran is right.

206
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:55,600
You've helped this village for 20 years.

207
00:08:55,879 --> 00:08:57,240
Now it's time for the village to repay you.

208
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,240
Since the land's been taken back,

209
00:08:59,679 --> 00:09:01,919
let's give Old Liu a new position.

210
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,799
The village committee has decided

211
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,200
to hire you as

212
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:07,480
the curator of our Red Culture Hall.

213
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:10,320
Tell visitors about our village history.

214
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,120
Party Secretary,

215
00:09:11,639 --> 00:09:13,000
I have to thank you first.

216
00:09:13,519 --> 00:09:14,960
But I can't do this job.

217
00:09:15,679 --> 00:09:16,320
I'm bad with words.

218
00:09:16,519 --> 00:09:17,639
What could I possibly tell them?

219
00:09:18,279 --> 00:09:20,080
I really can't do cushy jobs.

220
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:21,559
I'll head back now.

221
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:22,919
Uncle Liu.

222
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:23,919
Uncle Liu!

223
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:25,120
Zhaxi, you're here.

224
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,080
Please don't leave.

225
00:09:26,279 --> 00:09:26,840
Uncle Liu.

226
00:09:27,399 --> 00:09:28,600
You won't take a cushy job.

227
00:09:30,559 --> 00:09:31,879
Then would you do some hard work?

228
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:36,120
My test field was almost wiped out before.

229
00:09:36,399 --> 00:09:37,600
You were the one who helped me.

230
00:09:37,919 --> 00:09:39,080
For highland farming,

231
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:41,639
the climate and soil microclimate are key.

232
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,360
Books taught us about sunlight and water,

233
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:46,600
but didn't teach us how, in a whirlwind,

234
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,559
to tie a clove hitch knot,

235
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:49,159
when to release tension,

236
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,360
or when to block the wind.

237
00:09:50,919 --> 00:09:51,480
Dr. Meiduo,

238
00:09:51,639 --> 00:09:53,080
So what you mean is,

239
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:56,440
I'll apply for rural revitalization funds

240
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:59,240
to build a highland crop nursery.

241
00:10:00,279 --> 00:10:00,799
Sure.

242
00:10:01,159 --> 00:10:01,960
I'll file the application right away.

243
00:10:03,799 --> 00:10:04,519
Uncle Liu,

244
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,960
but I'm short one chief grower.

245
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,279
No driving, no lecturing needed.

246
00:10:09,879 --> 00:10:13,080
Just manage the wind, water, and soil.

247
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:14,840
But this work is a bit tiring.

248
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,840
You'll need to toil out in the fields.

249
00:10:17,519 --> 00:10:18,200
Will you do it?

250
00:10:18,679 --> 00:10:19,080
Me?

251
00:10:22,279 --> 00:10:23,039
You know what?

252
00:10:24,159 --> 00:10:25,200
I've actually been thinking all along,

253
00:10:25,639 --> 00:10:26,519
We want to develop,

254
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,679
to revitalize, to be a model village.

255
00:10:30,399 --> 00:10:31,240
What are we striving for?

256
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,519
Isn't it just so that

257
00:10:34,799 --> 00:10:35,320
when we grow old,

258
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:36,759
when we're up in years,

259
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,200
and we look back,

260
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,240
we can say this life of ours

261
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,840
wasn't lived in vain,

262
00:10:44,279 --> 00:10:46,159
that we worked to bring others a better life,

263
00:10:46,159 --> 00:10:47,440
that we tried and fought hard.

264
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:48,600
Right?

265
00:10:56,879 --> 00:10:57,600
Uncle Liu,

266
00:10:57,879 --> 00:10:59,720
Just tell me, will you do it or not?

267
00:11:02,919 --> 00:11:03,480
I'll do it.

268
00:11:03,919 --> 00:11:05,679
All I know in this life is farming.

269
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:06,960
If I don't farm,

270
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,159
what else can I do?

271
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:10,320
Great.
